     RNTrack installation instructions
     $Id$

tar jxf rntrack-version.tar.bz2
cd rntrack-version/MakeFiles/YourSystem
(for example, for linux: cd rntrack-version/MakeFiles/linux)
make

Make options:

CONFIG="path/to/cfg"       - Default config path. If not defined, using "~/fido/etc/rntrack.cfg" under *NIX
                             "%USERPROFILE%\fido\rntrack.cfg" under Windows or "rntrack.cfg" under other OS.

ENABLE_SCRIPTS=1           - Enable Perl scripts support (currently not available on WIN32 and OS/2)
ENABLE_LOG_PID=1           - Enable pid logging (ex: 21.04.2004 12:02:39 [212] --- RNtrack 1.11/LNX started.)
ENABLE_SYSLOG_LOG_FORMAT=1 - Use syslog-like log style (ex: Apr 04 22:00:02 --- RNtrack 1.11/LNX started.)

This options are disabled by default.
